      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "Hidaya Foundation's financial health is characterized by high liquidity and low liability, reporting <cite id=\"12\">total assets of $4,333,942</cite> against <cite id=\"13\">liabilities of only $7,808</cite>. This fiscal discipline allows the organization to maintain <cite id=\"14\">3.5 months of working capital</cite>, providing a stable foundation for its international operations. Furthermore, the organization has demonstrated consistent growth with a <cite id=\"15\">3-year revenue CAGR of 11.5%</cite>, indicating increasing donor trust and capacity to scale."
      ],
      "summary": "Founded in <cite id=\"1\">1999</cite>, the Hidaya Foundation is a humanitarian organization dedicated to providing <cite id=\"2\">educational, social welfare, and charitable assistance</cite> to economically depressed regions. The organization operates at a significant scale, reporting <cite id=\"3\">total revenue of $15,472,301</cite> in the 2023 tax year. Hidaya is distinguished by its lean operational model, maintaining a <cite id=\"4\">program expense ratio of 95.0%</cite>, which ensures that the vast majority of donor funds are directed toward direct service delivery rather than administrative overhead. Their reach is global, with active programs in <cite id=\"5\">Pakistan, Bangladesh, Sri Lanka, Afghanistan, and several African nations</cite> including Somalia and Ethiopia. As a <cite id=\"6\">Zakat-eligible entity</cite>, the foundation provides a structured platform for Muslim donors to fulfill their religious obligations across categories such as <cite id=\"7\">fuqara, masakin, and fisabilillah</cite>. The organization's efficiency is further highlighted by its <cite id=\"8\">fundraising efficiency of $0.02 per $1 raised</cite>, one of the lowest costs in the humanitarian sector. Beyond emergency relief, Hidaya invests in long-term stability through <cite id=\"9\">self-employment and healthcare programs</cite>, aiming to lift families out of poverty permanently.",
